<title>Meta的Muse Spark 1.1在编程方面超越GLM-5.2，且成本略低</title>
<link>https://the-decoder.com/metas-muse-spark-1-1-outperforms-glm-5-2-in-coding-and-costs-slightly-less/</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">https://the-decoder.com/?p=37627</guid>
<pubDate>Sat, 11 Jul 2026 08:28:12 +0000</pubDate>
<source>the-decoder.com</source>
<description><![CDATA[【the-decoder.com】Meta的Muse Spark 1.1在人工智能分析指数上得分为51分，三个月内提升了8分。在编程方面，它以71.3分的成绩略胜GLM-5.2，每项任务成本更低，仅为0.26美元。幻觉率从73%降至38%。本文《Meta's Muse Spark 1.1 outperforms GLM-5.2 in coding and costs slightly less》最初发表于The Decoder。<br/><br/><a href="https://the-decoder.com/metas-muse-spark-1-1-outperforms-glm-5-2-in-coding-and-costs-slightly-less/">阅读原文</a>]]></description>
</item>
<item>
<title>OpenAI承认ChatGPT Work上线“并非尽善尽美”，正紧急修复用户体验与成本问题</title>
<link>https://the-decoder.com/openai-admits-it-didnt-get-everything-quite-right-with-chatgpt-work-launch-and-scrambles-to-fix-ux-and-costs/</link>
<guid isPermaLink="false">https://the-decoder.com/?p=37623</guid>
<pubDate>Sat, 11 Jul 2026 08:01:09 +0000</pubDate>
<source>the-decoder.com</source>
<description><![CDATA[【the-decoder.com】在ChatGPT Work及GPT-5.6 Sol发布后，OpenAI承认存在重大缺陷：计算资源消耗过高、聊天与项目切换至桌面界面时体验混乱、Codex与ChatGPT Work界限模糊，以及现有工作流程出现退化。据报道，GPT-5.6 Sol在某些情况下会自行删除用户未授权的数据。本文《OpenAI admits it "didn't get everything quite right" with ChatGPT Work launch and scrambles to fix UX and costs》最初发表于The Decoder。<br/><br/><a href="https://the-decoder.com/openai-admits-it-didnt-get-everything-quite-right-with-chatgpt-work-launch-and-scrambles-to-fix-ux-and-costs/">阅读原文</a>]]></description>
</item>
